Protogoniomorpha anacardii, the clouded mother-of-pearl, is a species of Nymphalidae butterfly found in tropical Africa.The wingspan is 55–68 mm for males and 65–75 mm for females.Its flight period is year-round, peaking in summer and autumn.The species larval food is Asystasia, Brillantaisia, Isoglossa, Justicia, Mimulopsis, and Paulowilhelmia species.